# Chezmoi ignore patterns
# Files and directories that should not be tracked by chezmoi
#
# NOTE: Some sensitive files listed below can be encrypted and tracked instead of ignored.
# To encrypt them, remove the pattern from this file and use:
#   ./scripts/chezmoi_encrypt_secrets.sh
# Then add them with encryption enabled.

# Sensitive configuration files
# ==============================
# 
# IMPORTANT: Files listed below are IGNORED by default.
# If you want to BACKUP these files (encrypted), you must:
#   1. Remove the pattern from this file
#   2. Run: ./scripts/chezmoi_encrypt_secrets.sh
#   3. Select option 2 or 4 to encrypt the file
#
# See BACKUP_GUIDE.md for complete instructions.

# Always ignore (too sensitive or auto-generated):
**/configstore/**          # Contains API keys and tokens
**/github-copilot/**       # Contains GitHub tokens
**/firebase/**             # Contains Firebase credentials

# Can be encrypted if you want to back them up:
# Comment out (or remove) the lines below if you want to encrypt these files
# **/.ssh/id_*               # SSH private keys (commented = can encrypt)
# **/.ssh/*_rsa              # SSH RSA keys (commented = can encrypt)
# **/.ssh/*_ed25519          # SSH Ed25519 keys (commented = can encrypt)
# **/.aws/credentials        # AWS credentials (commented = can encrypt)
# **/.gcloud/**              # GCloud configs (commented = can encrypt)

# Cache and temporary files
**/.DS_Store
**/cache/**
**/tmp/**
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*~
**/.vim/autoload/**

# Large binary files
**/*.hprof
**/*.log
**/*.sqlite
**/*.db

# OS-specific files
**/Library/**
**/Applications/**

# Build artifacts
**/node_modules/**
**/.venv/**
**/__pycache__/**

# IDE and editor files
**/.idea/**
**/.vscode/**
**/*.code-workspace

# Git files (already tracked by git)
**/.git/**

# Homebrew bundle lock
**/Brewfile.lock.json

